posts.name: Mykah
posts.cooked:
Yep, as it is you don‚Äôt have any gain set for any of the PIDF Components.

double kP = 0.0,

kI = 0.0,

kD = 0.0,

kIz = 0.0,

kFF = 0.0,

You generally start with increasing the Proportional gain (kP) until you are either happy with the result or you start getting oscillations, then you add Derivative (kD) to smooth out the Oscillations to get to a quick steady state, and finally you add Integral (kI) to help deal with if the steady state isn‚Äôt quite at your setpoint.

Both of our Position PIDs this year worked well enough with only Proportional control, so we didn‚Äôt bother adding any Integral or Derivative gain (leaving them at zero).
